# Infrastructure

<%= image_tag 'busfactory.jpg' %>

GOV.UK Pay running on [GOV.UK Platform as a Service](https://www.cloud.service.gov.uk/) uses a hybrid infrastructure.

Some infrastructure components reside in AWS, while application services run on GOV.UK PaaS.

### AWS Components

AWS components are managed by the GOV.UK Pay team. These include:

- Route 53 DNS
- CloudFront CDN / Cache
- AWS WAF / Shield
- S3
- Kinesis Firehose
- SQS
- Lambda
- RDS

### GOV.UK PaaS / CloudFoundry Components

The infrastructure for these services is managed by the GOV.UK PaaS team:

- All microservice applications
- Scheduled tasks
- Application log services
- Application metric services
- Application credentials

